# Clean Hands, Dirty Money — environment template
# This game is a self-contained, transferable unit. It owns its OWN secrets — it does
# NOT read from the WARP factory's Operations/.secrets. At runtime the serverless
# functions read these from the Vercel PROJECT ENV (Settings -> Environment Variables).
# For local dev, copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values (gitignored).
#
# NOTE: the /api/ functions themselves were NOT recovered into this repo (see README
# CAVEAT). These are the env var NAMES the live functions are inferred to need based on
# the client calls in index.html (/api/track and /api/ref). Reconcile against the
# canonical function source from the builder chat before relying on this list.

# --- Owned data store (Vercel Edge Config) ---
# Vercel team that owns the project + edge config store(s)
EC_TEAM=team_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Analytics store — the /api/track aggregate counters
A_EC_ID=ecfg_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Referral store — the /api/ref code/pending-claim ledger (refer / claim / stats)
REF_EC_ID=ecfg_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Account token used by the functions to read/write Edge Config (SENSITIVE — never commit).
# Use a long-lived Vercel API token (Account -> Settings -> Tokens) so it does not expire.
EC_TOKEN=

# --- Private dashboard / Control Room read key ---
# Guards GET /api/track?action=report. Hand this to the Control Room as a READ-ONLY key.
DASH_KEY=changeme
